---
const pageTitle = "Fix Flaky Tests at the System Level | QA ALIGN";
const pageDescription =
  "QA ALIGN helps engineering teams turn unreliable automation and noisy CI into deterministic test signal, artifact-driven diagnosis, and clear release decisions.";
import ProofArtifact from '../../../components/ProofArtifact.astro';
import '../../../styles/components.css';
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width,initial-scale=1" />
    <!-- Google tag (gtag.js) -->
    <!-- Google tag (GA4) -->
    <script async src="https://www.googletagmanager.com/gtag/js?id=G-QHBTSD452X"></script>
    <script is:inline>
      window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
      function gtag(){dataLayer.push(arguments);}
      gtag('js', new Date());
      gtag('config', 'G-QHBTSD452X');
    </script>
    <title>{pageTitle}</title>
    <meta name="description" content={pageDescription} />
    <style>
      :root {
        --qa-bg: #0b0e14;
        --qa-panel: #121827;
        --qa-panel-2: #0f1522;
        --qa-text: #e6e9ef;
        --qa-muted: #aab2c5;
        --qa-border: #24304d;
        --qa-link: #7aa2ff;
        --qa-accent: #7aa2ff;
        --qa-accent-2: #9bb8ff;
        --qa-shadow: 0 16px 40px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.28);
      }

      * { box-sizing: border-box; }
      html { scroll-behavior: smooth; }

      body {
        margin: 0;
        background: var(--qa-bg);
        color: var(--qa-text);
        font-family: ui-sans-serif, system-ui, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", sans-serif;
        line-height: 1.5;
      }

      a { color: inherit; }

      .site-shell { padding: 2rem 0 4rem; }
      .qa-container { width: min(1180px, calc(100% - 2rem)); margin: 0 auto; }

      .qa-section, .qa-hero, .qa-cta-band { margin: 0 0 2rem; }

      .qa-hero, .qa-section, .qa-cta-band__content {
        border: 1px solid var(--qa-border);
        background: linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(18, 24, 39, 0.98), rgba(11, 14, 20, 0.98));
        border-radius: 24px;
        box-shadow: var(--qa-shadow);
      }

      .qa-hero {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 1.2fr 0.8fr;
        gap: 2rem;
        padding: 2.25rem;
        align-items: center;
      }

      .qa-section { padding: 2rem; }

      .qa-section--alt {
        background: linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(15, 21, 34, 0.98), rgba(11, 14, 20, 0.98));
      }

      .qa-section__header {
        max-width: 860px;
        margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
      }

      .qa-eyebrow {
        margin: 0 0 0.6rem;
        color: var(--qa-accent-2);
        font-size: 0.8rem;
        font-weight: 700;
        letter-spacing: 0.12em;
        text-transform: uppercase;
      }

      .qa-hero h1, .qa-section h2, .qa-cta-band h2 {
        margin: 0;
        line-height: 1.08;
        letter-spacing: -0.02em;
      }

      .qa-hero h1 {
        font-size: clamp(2.25rem, 5vw, 4rem);
        max-width: 12ch;
      }

      .qa-section h2, .qa-cta-band h2 {
        font-size: clamp(1.6rem, 3vw, 2.6rem);
        max-width: 24ch;
      }

      .qa-lead, .qa-copy, .qa-card p, .qa-offer-card, .qa-cta-band p {
        color: var(--qa-muted);
        line-height: 1.7;
        font-size: 1.02rem;
      }

      .qa-lead {
        max-width: 62ch;
        margin: 1rem 0 1.25rem;
        font-size: 1.08rem;
      }

      .qa-copy p { margin: 0 0 1rem; }
      .qa-copy p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }

      .qa-copy--narrow {
        max-width: 760px;
      }

      .qa-proof-list, .qa-list, .qa-flow {
        margin: 0;
        padding-left: 1.15rem;
        color: var(--qa-text);
      }

      .qa-proof-list {
        display: grid;
        gap: 0.5rem;
        margin-bottom: 1.4rem;
      }

      .qa-list li, .qa-flow li, .qa-proof-list li { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }

      .qa-actions {
        display: flex;
        flex-wrap: wrap;
        gap: 0.9rem;
        margin-top: 1.25rem;
      }

      .qa-actions--section { margin-top: 1.5rem; }

      .qa-btn {
        display: inline-flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: center;
        min-height: 46px;
        padding: 0.82rem 1.15rem;
        border-radius: 999px;
        border: 1px solid var(--qa-border);
        text-decoration: none;
        font-weight: 700;
        transition: transform 0.15s ease, border-color 0.15s ease, background 0.15s ease;
      }

      .qa-btn:hover {
        transform: translateY(-1px);
        border-color: var(--qa-accent);
      }

      .qa-btn--primary {
        color: #08111f;
        background: linear-gradient(180deg, var(--qa-accent-2), var(--qa-accent));
        border-color: transparent;
      }

      .qa-btn--secondary {
        color: var(--qa-text);
        background: rgba(122, 162, 255, 0.08);
      }

      .qa-btn--full { width: 100%; }

      .qa-diagram-card, .qa-offer-card, .qa-card {
        border: 1px solid var(--qa-border);
        background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.02);
        border-radius: 20px;
      }

      .qa-diagram-card { padding: 1.4rem; }

      .qa-logo-card {
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: center;
        min-height: 132px;
        padding: 22px;
        border: 1px solid var(--qa-border);
        border-radius: 18px;
        background:
          radial-gradient(circle at center, rgba(122, 162, 255, 0.26), transparent 58%),
          rgba(15, 21, 34, 0.86);
        box-shadow: var(--qa-shadow);
        margin-bottom: 18px;
      }

      .qa-logo-card img {
        max-width: 340px;
        width: 100%;
        height: auto;
        display: block;
      }

      .qa-diagram-card__eyebrow {
        margin: 0 0 0.45rem;
        color: var(--qa-accent-2);
        font-size: 0.78rem;
        font-weight: 700;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: 0.12em;
      }

      .qa-diagram-card h2 {
        margin: 0 0 1rem;
        font-size: 1.4rem;
        line-height: 1.2;
      }

      .qa-grid {
        display: grid;
        gap: 1rem;
      }

      .qa-grid--3 { grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr)); }
      .qa-grid--4 { grid-template-columns: repeat(4, minmax(0, 1fr)); }

      .qa-card { padding: 1.2rem; }

      .qa-card h3, .qa-offer-card h3 {
        margin: 0 0 0.6rem;
        font-size: 1.02rem;
        line-height: 1.3;
      }

      .qa-card p { margin: 0; }

      .qa-two-col {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 1.3fr 0.7fr;
        gap: 1rem;
        align-items: start;
      }

      .qa-offer-card { padding: 1.35rem; }

      .qa-not-fit {
        display: flex;
        flex-wrap: wrap;
        gap: 0.75rem;
      }
      .report-preview {
  padding: 56px 0 34px;
}

.report-preview__shell {
  max-width: 980px;
  margin: 0 auto;
  text-align: center;
}

.report-preview__eyebrow {
  margin: 0 0 10px;
  font-size: 13px;
  font-weight: 800;
  letter-spacing: 0.18em;
  color: #7aa2ff;
}

.report-preview__title {
  margin: 0;
  font-size: 42px;
  line-height: 1.08;
  color: #e6e9ef;
}

.report-preview__desc {
  margin: 14px auto 26px;
  max-width: 760px;
  color: #aab2c5;
  font-size: 18px;
  line-height: 1.6;
}

.report-preview__frame {
  border-radius: 18px;
  overflow: hidden;
  border: 1px solid #24304d;
  box-shadow:
    0 30px 90px rgba(0,0,0,.55),
    0 0 40px rgba(80,120,255,.10);
}

.video-frame {
  aspect-ratio: 16 / 9;
  width: 100%;
  background: #000;
}

.video-frame iframe {
  width: 100%;
  height: 100%;
  border: 0;
}

      .qa-not-fit span {
        display: inline-flex;
        padding: 0.7rem 0.95rem;
        border-radius: 999px;
        border: 1px solid var(--qa-border);
        background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.02);
        color: var(--qa-muted);
      }

      .qa-cta-band__content {
        padding: 2rem;
        text-align: center;
      }

      .qa-cta-band__content h2 {
        max-width: 22ch;
        margin-left: auto;
        margin-right: auto;
      }

      .qa-cta-band__content p {
        max-width: 760px;
        margin: 0.9rem auto 0;
      }

      .qa-cta-band .qa-actions { justify-content: center; }

      @media (max-width: 980px) {
        .qa-hero, .qa-two-col, .qa-grid--3, .qa-grid--4 {
          grid-template-columns: 1fr;
        }

        .qa-hero h1, .qa-section h2, .qa-cta-band h2 {
          max-width: none;
        }
      }

      @media (max-width: 640px) {
        .site-shell { padding-top: 1rem; }
        .qa-container { width: min(100% - 1rem, 1180px); }

        .qa-hero, .qa-section, .qa-cta-band__content {
          padding: 1.25rem;
          border-radius: 18px;
        }

        .qa-actions { flex-direction: column; }
        .qa-btn { width: 100%; }
      }
    </style>
  </head>

  <body>
    <main class="site-shell">
      <div class="qa-container">
        <section class="qa-hero">
          <div class="qa-hero__content">
            <p class="qa-eyebrow">QA ALIGN</p>
            <h1>Fix Flaky Tests at the System Level</h1>
            <p class="qa-lead">
              QA ALIGN helps engineering teams turn unreliable automation and noisy CI
              into deterministic test signal, artifact-driven diagnosis, and clear
              release decisions.
            </p>

            <ul class="qa-proof-list">
              <li>API-first state setup</li>
              <li>CI-integrated diagnosability</li>
              <li>Structured failure outputs</li>
              <li>GO / WARN / BLOCK release logic</li>
            </ul>

            <div class="qa-actions">
              <a class="qa-btn qa-btn--primary qa-btn--full" href="https://buy.stripe.com/eVqcN74vpe5O1Eg86GdAk01">
                Run Assessment — $149
              </a>
              <a class="qa-btn qa-btn--secondary" href="/#sprint-5">
                See Sprint Proof
              </a>
            </div>
          </div>

          <aside class="qa-hero__visual" aria-label="QA ALIGN system flow">
            <div class="qa-logo-card">
              <img src="/qa-align-logo.png" alt="QA ALIGN" />
            </div>

            <div class="qa-diagram-card">
              <p class="qa-diagram-card__eyebrow">System Flow</p>
              <h2>From noisy failures to release clarity</h2>
              <ol class="qa-flow">
                <li>Unstable tests and unreliable CI signal</li>
                <li>Deterministic setup and controlled execution</li>
                <li>Artifact capture and structured failure outputs</li>
                <li>Clear release decision: GO / WARN / BLOCK</li>
              </ol>
            </div>
          </aside>
        </section>

        <section class="qa-section">
          <div class="qa-section__header">
            <p class="qa-eyebrow">The Core Problem</p>
            <h2>Flaky tests are usually not a test problem. They are a system problem.</h2>
          </div>

          <div class="qa-copy">
            <p>
              Most teams do not actually have a few flaky tests. They have a trust
              problem caused by unstable state, weak artifact quality, brittle test
              design, and CI pipelines that produce noise instead of signal.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="qa-grid qa-grid--4">
            <article class="qa-card">
              <h3>Local pass, CI fail</h3>
              <p>
                The suite behaves differently across environments because the system
                contract is weak.
              </p>
            </article>

            <article class="qa-card">
              <h3>Reruns become normal</h3>
              <p>
                The first failure does not tell a complete story, so reruns become part
                of the workflow.
              </p>
            </article>

            <article class="qa-card">
              <h3>Release confidence drops</h3>
              <p>
                Automation exists, but engineering leaders still cannot trust the signal
                during release decisions.
              </p>
            </article>

            <article class="qa-card">
              <h3>Modernization pressure rises</h3>
              <p>
                The team wants to move forward, but the current foundation is too unstable
                to scale safely.
              </p>
            </article>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="qa-section qa-section--alt">
          <div class="qa-section__header">
            <p class="qa-eyebrow">What QA ALIGN Changes</p>
            <h2>Not generic QA automation. A deterministic system for diagnosable release signal.</h2>
          </div>

          <div class="qa-grid qa-grid--3">
            <article class="qa-card">
              <h3>API-First State Setup</h3>
              <p>
                Tests start from known conditions instead of depending on UI setup,
                leftover state, or execution order.
              </p>
            </article>

            <article class="qa-card">
              <h3>Artifact-Driven Failure Analysis</h3>
              <p>
                Failures can be diagnosed from evidence without depending on another run
                to explain the last run.
              </p>
            </article>

            <article class="qa-card">
              <h3>Structured Failure Outputs</h3>
              <p>
                Results are readable by humans and systems, making triage and release
                reasoning more consistent.
              </p>
            </article>

            <article class="qa-card">
              <h3>CI-Integrated Diagnosability</h3>
              <p>
                Evidence shows up where release decisions actually happen, not in
                disconnected local debugging sessions.
              </p>
            </article>

            <article class="qa-card">
              <h3>Release Gate Decisioning</h3>
              <p>
                Test output becomes decision-ready guidance: GO, WARN, or BLOCK.
              </p>
            </article>

            <article class="qa-card">
              <h3>Modernization Without Disruption</h3>
              <p>
                Improve trust and diagnosability first, then expand intelligently without
                destabilizing delivery.
              </p>
            </article>
          </div>
        </section>
        <section class="report-preview" aria-labelledby="video-demo-title">
          <div class="wrap">
            <div class="report-preview__shell">
        
              <p id="video-demo-title" class="report-preview__eyebrow">
                LIVE DIAGNOSTIC EXPLAINER
              </p>
        
              <h2 class="report-preview__title">
                See How Flaky Systems Get Diagnosed
              </h2>
        
              <p class="report-preview__desc">
                A short walkthrough showing how hidden anti-patterns create instability,
                false failures, and low trust in automation.
              </p>
        
              <div class="report-preview__frame">
                <div class="video-frame">
                  <iframe
                    src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/LNqhtPH8bvY?rel=0&modestbranding=1"
                    title="QA ALIGN Flake Diagnosis Demo"
                    loading="lazy"
                    allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share"
                    allowfullscreen
                  ></iframe>
                </div>
              </div>
        
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>
        <section class="qa-section">
          <div class="qa-section__header">
            <p class="qa-eyebrow">What I Diagnose First</p>
            <h2>The anti-patterns that quietly break automation trust</h2>
          </div>

          <div class="qa-grid qa-grid--3">
            <article class="qa-card">
              <h3>Shared State and Order Dependence</h3>
              <p>
                Tests only pass in a certain sequence or after prior runs have set up the
                right conditions.
              </p>
            </article>

            <article class="qa-card">
              <h3>Local vs CI Drift</h3>
              <p>
                The suite behaves one way on a laptop and another way inside the actual
                delivery pipeline.
              </p>
            </article>

            <article class="qa-card">
              <h3>Brittle UI Interaction Patterns</h3>
              <p>
                Locators, setup flow, or timing assumptions are too fragile to produce
                stable signal.
              </p>
            </article>

            <article class="qa-card">
              <h3>Rerun-Based Debugging</h3>
              <p>
                The team needs another execution just to understand the previous failure.
              </p>
            </article>

            <article class="qa-card">
              <h3>Weak Artifacts</h3>
              <p>
                Screenshots, logs, traces, and outputs do not tell a coherent story when
                something breaks.
              </p>
            </article>

            <article class="qa-card">
              <h3>No Release Decision Layer</h3>
              <p>
                Automation produces pass/fail output, but not a defensible release
                recommendation.
              </p>
            </article>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="qa-section qa-section--alt">
          <div class="qa-section__header">
            <p class="qa-eyebrow">The Real Goal</p>
            <h2>The goal is not more automation. The goal is trustworthy release signal.</h2>
          </div>

          <div class="qa-copy qa-copy--narrow">
            <p>
              A larger suite does not solve instability. The real objective is a system
              that gives engineering leaders confidence in what failed, why it failed,
              what evidence supports it, and whether the release should proceed.
            </p>
            <p>
              That is the difference between automation volume and automation trust.
            </p>
          </div>
        </section>
        <section class="qa-section qa-section--alt">
          <div class="report-preview">
            <div class="report-preview__frame">
              <img
                src="/images/assessment-report.png"
                alt="QA Automation Assessment Report preview"
              />
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="qa-section">
          <div class="qa-section__header">
            <p class="qa-eyebrow">Proof</p>
            <h2>Built from real system patterns, not generic promises</h2>
          </div>

          <div class="qa-copy">
            <p>
              QA ALIGN includes live runbooks and sprint-based proof showing how
              deterministic automation systems are designed, stabilized, and matured over
              time.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="qa-grid qa-grid--4">
            <article class="qa-card">
              <h3>Environment and Network Discipline</h3>
              <p>
                Clear runner-to-system boundaries, explicit environment targeting, and no
                false local shortcuts.
              </p>
            </article>

            <article class="qa-card">
              <h3>Artifact-First Failure Diagnostics</h3>
              <p>
                Failures are captured with enough evidence to support debugging without a
                rerun.
              </p>
            </article>

            <article class="qa-card">
              <h3>Parallel-Safe State Strategy</h3>
              <p>
                State is managed deliberately so tests remain independent and scalable.
              </p>
            </article>

            <article class="qa-card">
              <h3>Release Gate Decisioning</h3>
              <p>
                Automation output is translated into actionable release guidance instead
                of raw noise.
              </p>
            </article>
          </div>

        <div class="qa-actions">
          <a class="qa-btn qa-btn--primary" href="/offerings/diagnose-without-reruns/">
            Run Your Automation Assessment
          </a>
          <a class="qa-btn qa-btn--secondary" href="/#sprint-5">
            See Sprint Proof
          </a>
        </div>
        </section>

        <section class="qa-section qa-section--alt" id="technical-review">
          <div class="qa-section__header">
            <p class="qa-eyebrow">Offer</p>
            <h2>Start with a Technical Signal Review</h2>
          </div>

          <div class="qa-two-col">
            <div class="qa-copy">
              <p>
                A good first step is not a rewrite. It is a focused review of your
                current automation signal.
              </p>
              <p>In a Technical Signal Review, I look at:</p>
              <ul class="qa-list">
                <li>where trust is breaking down</li>
                <li>which anti-patterns are driving flake</li>
                <li>whether the suite is diagnosable from artifacts</li>
                <li>how release decisions are currently being made</li>
                <li>what the right first system correction should be</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <aside class="qa-offer-card">
              <p class="qa-eyebrow">What you get</p>
              <ul class="qa-list">
                <li>Trust-level assessment</li>
                <li>Key anti-pattern findings</li>
                <li>Likely sprint entry point</li>
                <li>Recommended first correction path</li>
              </ul>
              <a class="qa-btn qa-btn--primary qa-btn--full" href="https://buy.stripe.com/eVqcN74vpe5O1Eg86GdAk01">
                Run Assessment — $149
              </a>
            </aside>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="qa-section">
          <div class="qa-section__header">
            <p class="qa-eyebrow">Best Fit</p>
            <h2>Best fit for teams experiencing</h2>
          </div>

          <div class="qa-grid qa-grid--4">
            <article class="qa-card">
              <h3>Flaky test suites</h3>
              <p>
                Automation is running, but the team does not trust what it is saying.
              </p>
            </article>

            <article class="qa-card">
              <h3>Weak release confidence</h3>
              <p>
                There is no clean connection between test results and defensible release
                decisions.
              </p>
            </article>

            <article class="qa-card">
              <h3>Modernization pressure</h3>
              <p>
                The team needs to improve the system without destabilizing delivery.
              </p>
            </article>

            <article class="qa-card">
              <h3>Growing automation complexity</h3>
              <p>
                Playwright, Selenium, API, and CI layers are expanding faster than system
                discipline.
              </p>
            </article>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="qa-section qa-section--alt">
          <div class="qa-section__header">
            <p class="qa-eyebrow">Not a Fit</p>
            <h2>Not for teams looking for</h2>
          </div>

          <div class="qa-not-fit">
            <span>Low-cost generic QA execution</span>
            <span>Manual test outsourcing</span>
            <span>Test case volume without architecture change</span>
            <span>AI hype without operational discipline</span>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="qa-cta-band">
          <div class="qa-cta-band__content">
            <h2>
              If your automation runs but your team still cannot trust the signal, that is
              the system to fix.
            </h2>
            <p>
              QA ALIGN is built to turn unreliable automation into diagnosable evidence and
              clear release decisions.
            </p>
            <div class="qa-actions">
              <a class="qa-btn qa-btn--primary qa-btn--full" href="https://buy.stripe.com/eVqcN74vpe5O1Eg86GdAk01">
                Run Assessment — $149
              </a>
              <a class="qa-btn qa-btn--secondary" href="/#sprint-5">
                Review QA ALIGN Proof
              </a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>
      </div>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>